string_data:
PRIMARY: Two men, Daniel Knorr (22) and Noah Crane (19), face trial for daubing orange paint on Oxford University's historic Radcliffe Camera building during a Just Stop Oil protest in October. They are charged with criminal damage and possessing articles to damage property. The trial is scheduled for August 2025.

SECONDARY: No secondary protest actions mentioned.

OTHER FOCAL: The article focuses on the legal proceedings, noting the Radcliffe Camera is a 1730s building used as a Bodleian Library reading room.

TONE: The article maintains a neutral, factual tone focused on reporting the legal proceedings without editorial commentary on the protest.
